## Quickstart

```bash
# 1. Build CLI
cd cmd/grengo && go build -o ../../grengo .

# 2. Configure shared infra
cp .env.example .env   # set POSTGRES_PASSWORD

# 3. Create first tenant
./grengo new

# 4. Start everything
./grengo compose up

# 5. Access
# Site: http://localhost (or configured domain)
# Admin: Ctrl+G in browser, or management API on :9100
```

## Security

- Non-root container user (`appuser`) via `su-exec`
- Bind-mount ownership fixup at startup
- SHA-256 hashed passcode pair for remote management API
- nginx security headers on all responses
- Explicit CORS origin allowlist per tenant
- No wildcard domains
- Configurable DB connection pool limits
- File-based maintenance gate for traffic control
